notes: Conditional logic via Python control flow

components.name: Analyze Transactions
components.description: Reads daily transaction CSV files and calculates a fraud risk score for each batch.

components.name: Route Transaction
components.description: Evaluates the risk score and selects the next processing path (manual review or autoapprove).

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful risk score calculation.

components.name: Route to Manual Review
components.description: Loads highrisk transactions into the manual review queue for analyst assessment.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered when route_transaction selects the manualreview branch.

connections.purpose: Enqueue highrisk transactions for human review

components.name: Route to AutoApprove
components.description: Loads lowrisk transactions into the payment processing system for automatic approval.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered when route_transaction selects the autoapprove branch.

connections.purpose: Submit lowrisk transactions for automatic payment processing

components.name: Send Notification
components.description: Sends a final notification to the fraud detection team after both manual review and autoapprove paths complete.

upstream_policy.description: Executes after both branch paths finish without failures (trigger_rule='none_failed').

connections.purpose: Notify fraud detection team of pipeline completion

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

sources: Daily transaction CSV files stored on the file system
sinks: Manual review queue for highrisk transactions
Payment processing API for lowrisk transactions
Email/notification to the fraud detection team after processing completes
